---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

export const prerender = true;
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | AI Beauty Stylist"
  description="How AI Beauty Stylist handles photos, diagnosis data, usage data, and privacy controls."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container section-copy narrow">
      <span class="eyebrow">Privacy</span>
      <h1>Your photo is sensitive. The product is designed around that.</h1>
      <p>
        AI Beauty Stylist is designed to use your photo only for your own beauty recommendations, with clear controls for deletion and saved history.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="container grid-cards grid-cards-2">
      <article class="card coach-card">
        <h3>Photos</h3>
        <p>Your preview starts in the browser. Photo data is sent only when you ask for a diagnosis, then handled with limited retention and deletion controls.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card coach-card">
        <h3>Diagnosis data</h3>
        <p>Your diagnosis may include undertone, look recommendations, tutorial steps, product picks, and share-card text. Saved history requires clear consent.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card coach-card">
        <h3>Usage data</h3>
        <p>Basic request information may be used to prevent abuse, keep free limits fair, and improve the product. It is not sold as personal beauty data.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card coach-card">
        <h3>Deletion</h3>
        <p>The interface includes a delete action so you can remove your photo and related recommendations when you no longer want them kept.</p>
      </article>
    </div>

    <div class="container tutorial-cta-row top-gap">
      <a class="btn" href="/try-on">Continue to Try-On</a>
      <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/terms">Terms of Service</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
